{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Enforce Standards Post-Task",
  "description": "After a spec task completes, reviews all written files for ownership boundaries, naming conventions, code smells, and security.",
  "version": "1.1.0",
  "when": {
    "type": "postTaskExecution"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Review all files modified during this task for compliance:\n\n1. File ownership — did the agent only write within its domain? (system-architect: src/shared/, src/config/, docs/adr/ | frontend-dev: src/components/, src/hooks/, src/pages/, src/App.tsx | backend-dev: src/api/, src/services/, src/models/, src/middleware/ | ui-designer: src/styles/, src/design-system/, docs/design/ | qa-agent: e2e/, playwright.config.ts)\n2. Naming — kebab-case for .ts files, PascalCase for .tsx components\n3. Code smells — functions >20 lines, parameter lists >3, duplicated code\n4. Security — no hardcoded secrets, PII, or magic values\n5. Imports — flow inward toward shared/, no circular deps\n\nRun `git diff --name-only` to see what changed. Report any violations found."
  }
}